{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef"]]},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"new"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"identifier","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"text":">?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib11TimeZoneRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TimeZoneRef"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Type Method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:4GLib11TimeZoneRefV3new10identifierACSgSPys4Int8VGSg_tFZ","title":"new(identifier:)"},"abstract":[{"text":"Creates a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" corresponding to "},{"code":"identifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"type":"text","text":" cannot be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"parsed or loaded, "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"new","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">? = nil) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib11TimeZoneRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TimeZoneRef"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"text":" can either be an RFC3339\/ISO 8601 time offset or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"something that would pass as a valid value for the ","type":"text"},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" environment"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"variable (including "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":").","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Windows, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"type":"text","text":" can also be the unlocalized name of a time"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"zone for standard time, for example “Pacific Standard Time”.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Valid RFC3339 time offsets are "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Z\""},{"type":"text","text":" (for UTC) or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"±hh:mm\""},{"text":".  ISO 8601 additionally specifies","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"±hhmm\""},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"±hh\""},{"text":".  Offsets are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"time values to be added to Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) to get","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the local time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In UNIX, the "},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable typically corresponds"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to the name of a file in the zoneinfo database, an absolute path to a file"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"somewhere else, or a string in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"“std offset [dst [offset],start[\/time],end[\/time]]” (POSIX) format.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"There  are  no spaces in the specification. The name of standard","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and daylight savings time zone must be three or more alphabetic"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"characters. Offsets are time values to be added to local time to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"get Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) and should be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"[±]hh[[:]mm[:ss]]\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".  Dates are either","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"Jn\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (Julian day with n between 1 and 365, leap"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"years not counted), ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"n\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (zero-based Julian day","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with n between 0 and 365) or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Mm.w.d\""},{"text":" (day d","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(0 <= d <= 6) of week w (1 <= w <= 5) of month m (1 <= m <= 12), day"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"0 is a Sunday).  Times are in local wall clock time, the default is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"02:00:00.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Windows, the “tzn[+|–]hh"},{"identifier":"#dzn","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"” format is used, but also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"accepts POSIX format.  The Windows format uses US rules for all time"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"zones; daylight savings time is 60 minutes behind the standard time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with date and time of change taken from Pacific Standard Time.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Offsets are time values to be added to the local time to get"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Coordinated Universal Time (UTC)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"g_time_zone_new_local()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" calls this function with the value of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TZ"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable. This function itself is independent of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the value of "},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", but if ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" then "},{"code":"\/etc\/localtime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be consulted to discover the correct time zone on UNIX and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"registry will be consulted or "},{"code":"GetTimeZoneInformation()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be used","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to get the local time zone on Windows."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If intervals are not available, only time zone rules from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TZ"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"environment variable or other means, then they will be computed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"from year 1900 to 2037.  If the maximum year for the rules is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"available and it is greater than 2037, then it will followed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"instead.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc3339#section-5.6","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for a precise definition of valid RFC3339 time offsets"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(the "},{"code":"time-offset","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" expansion) and ISO 8601 for the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"full list of valid time offsets.  See"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/www.gnu.org\/s\/libc\/manual\/html_node\/TZ-Variable.html"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for an explanation of the possible","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TZ"},{"text":" environment variable. See","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"http:\/\/msdn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx","type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for the list of time zones on Windows."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You should release the return value by calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_time_zone_unref()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when you are done with it."}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timezoneref\/new(identifier:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/new(identifier:)"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","references":{"http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3339#section-5.6":{"identifier":"http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc3339#section-5.6","title":"RFC3339 §5.6","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"RFC3339 §5.6"}],"url":"http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc3339#section-5.6"},"#dzn":{"identifier":"#dzn","title":":mm[:ss]","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":":mm[:ss]","type":"text"}],"url":"#dzn"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeZone":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"text":" represents a time zone, at no particular point in time.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timezone","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TimeZone","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"TimeZone","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeZone"}]},"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx":{"identifier":"http:\/\/msdn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx","title":"Microsoft Time Zone Index Values","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Microsoft Time Zone Index Values","type":"text"}],"url":"http:\/\/msdn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeZoneRef":{"title":"TimeZoneRef","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TimeZoneRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timezoneref","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeZoneRef"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"GTimeZone","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" represents a time zone, at no particular point in time.","type":"text"}]},"http://www.gnu.org/s/libc/manual/html_node/TZ-Variable.html":{"identifier":"http:\/\/www.gnu.org\/s\/libc\/manual\/html_node\/TZ-Variable.html","title":"The GNU C Library manual","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The GNU C Library manual"}],"url":"http:\/\/www.gnu.org\/s\/libc\/manual\/html_node\/TZ-Variable.html"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeZoneRef/new(identifier:)":{"kind":"symbol",